	Joint Standing Committee on the Financial Management of Parliament: Briefings by Secretary to Parliament on: progress made in the drafting of regulations in terms of the Financial Management of Parliament and Provincial Legislatures Act (FMPPLA); progress made in the development of a framework for the processing of Parliament’s budget; the role of the Treasury Advice Office, and progress made in its establishment; and the drafting of the Strategic Plan of the Sixth Parliament ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENT OF THE REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICAEnquiries: Moloto Mothapo 082 370 6930 The room in which a House meets to debate is called a “Chamber”.Read more